    • Constructor Detail

      • Main

        public Main()
        Main reader functions.
        Before any of these functions can be used, the reader has to be Module.isPlugged() and Module.isPowered()

    • Method Detail

      • isInitialized

        public boolean isInitialized()
        Checks if the module is plugged in, powered, the reader is initialized and tests the connection
        This sends a command to the reader and waits for the answer.
        Do not call this function too often as it will block other reader communications.
        Returns:
        true if the reader is ready to use

      • init

        public Ipj_Error init()
               throws java.lang.IllegalStateException
        Initialize the reader.
        This has to be called before any other interaction with the reader can take place
        Do not call this method from UI thread!
        Returns:
        Ipj_Error
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - when called from UI thread

      • deInit

        public Ipj_Error deInit()
        Deinitialize and soft reset the RFID reader. This may take a few moments.
        You have to call init() to use the RFID reader again.
        Returns:
        Ipj_Error

      • startReader

        public Ipj_Error startReader()
        Starts a tag inventory.
        Tags in range are reported with JNIReporter The reader will be automatically stopped after 120s
        Returns:
        Ipj_Error

      • readTag

        public Ipj_Error readTag(int[] tagToSelect,
                         boolean selectedTagIsTID,
                         Enums.MemBank memBankToRead,
                         int index,
                         int count,
                         long password)
        Reads data from the specified tag memory.
        The specified data is reported with JNIAdvancedReporter.onTagOperationReport(Enums.IpjTagOperationReport)
        Parameters:
        tagToSelect - Selected tag ID, each array element contains 1 word (as HEX value). Max size is 16
        selectedTagIsTID - true, if selected tag ID is TID, false if selected tag ID is EPC
        memBankToRead - the memory bank to be read from
        index - index of the Enums.MemBank where the data should be read from
        count - number of words to read. Max value is 32
        password - long value of the password (2 words), can be 0 if no password is needed
        Returns:
        Ipj_Error result of the read process. Check in JNIAdvancedReporter.onTagOperationReport(Enums.IpjTagOperationReport) if the action was successful

      • killTag

        public Ipj_Error killTag(int[] tagToSelect,
                         boolean selectedTagIsTID,
                         long password)
        Kills the selected tag.
        Parameters:
        tagToSelect - Selected tag ID, each array element contains 1 word (as HEX value). Max size is 16
        selectedTagIsTID - true, if selected tag ID is TID, false if selected tag ID is EPC
        password - long value of the password (2 words), must not be 0
        Returns:
        Ipj_Error result of the kill process. Check in JNIAdvancedReporter.onTagOperationReport(Enums.IpjTagOperationReport) if the action was successful

      • setLockOnTag

        public Ipj_Error setLockOnTag(int[] tagToSelect,
                              boolean selectedTagIsTID,
                              Enums.LockMode lockMode,
                              long password)
        Sets a Enums.LockMode to the whole tag
        Only some tags support this action, and most of these only allow to Enums.LockMode.PERMA_LOCKED the whole tag
        Parameters:
        tagToSelect - Selected tag ID, each array element contains 1 word (as HEX value). Max size is 16
        selectedTagIsTID - true, if selected tag ID is TID, false if selected tag ID is EPC
        lockMode - Enums.LockMode to use
        password - long value of the password (2 words), can be 0 if no password is needed
        Returns:
        Ipj_Error result of the lock process. Check in JNIAdvancedReporter.onTagOperationReport(Enums.IpjTagOperationReport) if the action was successful

      • setLockOnMemBank

        public Ipj_Error setLockOnMemBank(int[] tagToSelect,
                                  boolean selectedTagIsTID,
                                  Enums.MemBank memBankToLock,
                                  Enums.LockMode lockMode,
                                  long password)
        Sets a Enums.LockMode to the specified Enums.MemBank of the tag.
        Only some tags support this action, and most of these only allow to Enums.LockMode.PERMA_LOCKED the whole tag
        Parameters:
        tagToSelect - Selected tag ID, each array element contains 1 word (as HEX value). Max size is 16
        selectedTagIsTID - true, if selected tag ID is TID, false if selected tag ID is EPC
        memBankToLock - the Enums.MemBank on which the lock mode is set
        lockMode - Enums.LockMode to use
        password - long value of the password (2 words), can be 0 if no password is needed
        Returns:
        Ipj_Error result of the lock process. Check in JNIAdvancedReporter.onTagOperationReport(Enums.IpjTagOperationReport) if the action was successful

      • stopReader

        public Ipj_Error stopReader()
        Stops the tag inventory
        Returns:
        Ipj_Error

      • writeTag

        public Ipj_Error writeTag(int[] tagToSelect,
                          boolean selectedTagIsTID,
                          int[] dataToWrite,
                          Enums.MemBank memBankToWrite,
                          int index,
                          long password)
        Writes new data on the specified tag memory
        After the data is written, a short inventory is executed which triggers JNIAdvancedReporter.onTagOperationReport(Enums.IpjTagOperationReport)
        Parameters:
        tagToSelect - Selected tag ID, each array element contains 1 word (as HEX value). Max size is 16
        selectedTagIsTID - true, if selected tag ID is TID, false if selected tag ID is EPC
        dataToWrite - data array to write to the selected ID, each array element contains 1 word (as HEX value)
        memBankToWrite - Enums.MemBank to be written to
        index - index of the memory bank where the data should be written to
        password - long value of the password (2 words), can be 0 if no password is needed
        Returns:
        Ipj_Error result of the write process. Check in JNIAdvancedReporter.onTagOperationReport(Enums.IpjTagOperationReport) if the action was successful

      • setCallback

        public void setCallback(JNIReporter reporter)
        Set the JNIReporter to get Callbacks from the RFID reader.
        It will report Ipj_Error in JNIReporter.onStatusMessage(Ipj_Error) if an error occurs. New tags are reported in JNIReporter.onTagUpdate(String, String, int, int, int)
        Parameters:
        reporter - JNIReporter

      • setAdvancedCallback

        public void setAdvancedCallback(JNIAdvancedReporter advancedReporter)
        Set a new JNIAdvancedReporter instance to receive Enums.IpjTagOperationReport from the reader
        Parameters:
        advancedReporter - instance of JNIAdvancedReporter
